
MAX7219 Stopwatch - Test Documentation

This directory contains project tests and helper scenarios for validating
stability, time accuracy, and peripherals.

Current Tests

- test_sdcard.cpp
	- Initializes SD card through SdCardManager
	- Writes a sample time into times.csv
	- Reads the file and prints content to serial

How To Run Tests

1. Connect ESP32 and verify the correct COM port.
2. Run the PlatformIO test command:
	 pio test -e esp32doit-devkit-v1

Note: test_sdcard.cpp is currently a hardware integration test
(depends on real SD card and pins), not an isolated unit test.

Recommended Next Tests

- Stopwatch logic
	- start/stop/reset state transitions
	- elapsed time accuracy within tolerance

- Display format
	- validation of m:ss:mmm format
	- render length and clipping for longer strings
	- flip on/off behavior without artifacts

- WebServer and result persistence
	- addElapsed/loadTimes/saveTimes consistency
	- edge cases (empty times.dat, corrupted record, MAX_TIMES limit)

Guidelines For Stable Tests

- Avoid delay in tests when possible.
- Use deterministic inputs and verify exact outputs.
- For hardware tests, clearly separate pin setup and expected behavior.
